01/11/2005
BERLIN, Germany -- The German government has nominated former Post and Telecommunications Minister Christian Schwarz-Schilling to succeed Paddy Ashdown as chief international officer in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). 
Ashdown has held the post since 2002 and is stepping down at the end of this year. 
Schwarz-Schilling, who served as a top envoy in BiH from 1995-2004, will be competing with candidates from the Netherlands, Italy and the Czech Republic. 
(Nezavisne novine - 01/11/05; DPA - 31/10/05)
